Subject:    <a href="?t=95837891400011&r=1&w=2">IETF-OSI-OR Agenda for Hawaii</a>
From:       <a href="?a=95837786600018&r=1&w=2">hagens () cs ! wisc ! edu</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198910">1989-10-20 14:18:59</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627058&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784627058&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

The IETF-OSI-OR group has changed its name to IETF-OSI-X.400.

IETF-OSI-X.400 will meet on tuesday (Halloween) in Hawaii 
(Bring your Phill Gross Mask!).

The morning will be spend reviewing scope and issues, whereas the afternoon
will be spent hammering out some problems. The Domain WG has been invited 
to attend the meeting. 

NOTE TO DOMAIN WG MEMBERS: if you are not interested in the problems
X.400 faces, then you should skip the morning. However, if you do, you
may not understand the motivation for the afternoon's work. Note also that
OSI bashing will be limited 1 BBU (British Bashing Unit -- approx 5 minutes)
per hour, not to exceed 8 BBUs in a 24 hour period.

NOTE TO ALL: please read RFC 987 before attending.

NOTE TO DOMAIN WG MEMBERS: please read ISO 7498-1, 7498-3, TR 8509,
9834 et al, 8824, 9594 et al, CCITT X.400, X.402, X.403, X.407,
X.408, X.411, X.413, X.419, X.420, GOSIP V2, NIST stable agreements,
and minutes of last NIST-RASIG, NIST-X.400, NIST-X.500 implementation
workshop meetings before attending.  :^)


Rob

				Agenda 
		IETF-OSI-X.400 (was OSI-OR)


am		+ Announcement of new name
		+ Status of the quest for "NREN"
		+ Review of Scope
			- 822 &lt;-&gt; X.400 gateway issues (RFC 987 and successors)
			- X.400 operational issues in a dual protocol internet

		+ Review of Issues
			- 822 &lt;-&gt; X.400 Gateways
				RFC 987 gateway background
				Table Maintenance
				Locating a Gateway
				ORAddress Structure

			- X.400 Operation
				Routing to destination or 822 gateway
				Use of Internet Technology
				Mixed Stacks
				MTA names
				Use of "NREN"

		+ Presentation of a new, unified address structure

pm		+ Enumerating, prioritizing, and discussion of major tasks

